Tabbouleh is a Middle Eastern dish made with fresh herbs and parsley. It's
Share to Facebook Share to Twitter Email Print
* 1/3 cup green onion, white and green parts thinly sliced
1. Soak the bulgur in lemon juice until it's completely immersed, set aside
2. Meanwhile, chop tomato, cucumber, onion as finely as possible.
3. To prepare the parsley, cut off the thick stems and discard. Chop parsley and remaining stem finely.
4. Check bulgur has softened. If not add more lemon juice and set aside for another 10 minutes.
5. Combine the finely chopped tomato, cucumber, onion and parsley into a bowl, add softened bulgur, salt, and drain juices.
6. Add remaining lemon juice, olive oil and pomegranate molasses mix well.
You can use lettuce leaves to act as 'wraps' for the tabbouleh.
If you don't have pomegranate molasses you can substitute with lime juice.
